President Donald J. Trump has announced his intent to nominate several individuals for key positions in his administration. Joseph Balash of Alaska is nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of the Interior, Land and Mineral Management. Samuel H. Clovis Jr. of Iowa is nominated to be Under Secretary of Agriculture for Research, Education, and Economics. Daniel Alan Craig of Maryland is nominated to be Deputy Administrator of the Federal Emergency Management Agency, Department of Homeland Security. J. Steven Dowd of Florida is nominated to be United States Director of the African Development Bank. Mark T. Esper of Virginia is nominated to be Secretary of the Army. Kathleen M. Fitzpatrick of the District of Columbia is nominated to be Ambassador Extraordinary and Plenipotentiary of the United States of America to the Democratic Republic of Timor-Leste. Daniel J. Kaniewski of Minnesota is nominated to be Deputy Administrator for National Preparedness of the Federal Emergency Management Agency, Department of Homeland Security. Anthony Kurta of Montana is nominated to be a Principal Deputy Under Secretary of Defense, Personnel and Readiness. Ted McKinney of Indiana is nominated to be Under Secretary of Agriculture for Trade and Foreign Agricultural Affairs. A. Wess Mitchell of Virginia is nominated to be an Assistant Secretary of State, European and Eurasian Affairs. Robert L. Wilkie of North Carolina is nominated to be Under Secretary of Defense for Personnel and Readiness.